  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3. When—Supply from Isa 64:2, \"As when.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "terrible things—(Ps 65:5).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "we looked not for—far exceeding the expectation of any of our nation; unparalleled before (Ex 34:10; Ps 68:8).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "camest down—on Mount Sinai.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "mountains flowed—Repeated from Isa 64:1; they pray God to do the very same things for Israel now as in former ages. Gesenius, instead of \"flowed\" here, and \"flow\" in Isa 64:1, translates from a different Hebrew root, \"quake … quaked\"; but \"fire\" melts and causes to flow, rather than to quake (Isa 64:2).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "When thou didst terrible things:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " this may relate to what he did among the Egyptians, though it be not recorded, and afterward in the wilderness. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
